{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place allspice, ground ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and 100 g granulated sugar in mixing bowl then grind <b>30 sec\/speed 10<b>.","Add fresh ginger, garlic and chilli then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Add onions and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add remaining 150 g granulated sugar, light brown sugar, vinegar and salt then, replace measuring cup with simmering basket, and cook <b>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 3<b>.","Add sultanas and mango then, replace measuring cup with simmering basket, and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>.","Pour into warm sterilised jars, seal and label. Allow chutney to mature for 4 weeks before serving as a condiment to many Indian dishes including curries and starters."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 tsp ground allspice","½ tsp ground ginger","½ tsp ground nutmeg","¼ tsp ground cinnamon","¼ tsp ground cloves","250 g granulated sugar","20 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","1 garlic clove","1 fresh red chilli, halved, deseeded","80 g onions, quartered","150 g light brown sugar","100 g white wine vinegar","¼ tsp fine sea salt","100 g sultanas","350 g ripe mangoes, diced (1 cm)"]}],"id":"r110687","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-R8s5RhcaqsY\/XZWYIJRuhYI\/AAAAAAAAd5I\/VRHsSjteA9APtyt5VrvH8BxYQg9Drxc_gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_0kN9lNWH3IGmxSH8.png","title":"Mango Chutney","publishedAt":"2017-04-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.5 g","fat":"2.8 g","uom":"per 1 total recipe","carbohydrates":"555.1 g","calories":"9540 kJ \/ 2280 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sterilised jam jars","hintsAndTricks":["Another classic, this goes with just about everything from poppadoms to your favourite curries, or simply slathered on cold meats and leftovers. Homemade, it contains a far more intense flavour as grinding the spices with sugar in your Thermomix is a great way to release the oils and aromas. Left to mature for a few weeks before using will only improve the flavour.","Once opened, the chutney should be stored in the fridge."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","50m","1 total recipe"]}